  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your oven to 160°C fan. Butter a 23cm springform cake tin then line the base with baking parchment."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the butter into cubes and put into a large saucepan. Pour in the Guinness, set over a low heat, stirring occasionally until melted, then whisk in the soft brown sugar and cocoa powder. Remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Crack the eggs into a jug, whisk in the yoghurt and vanilla extract then tip into the saucepan, along with the flour and bicarb. Whisk until a super smooth chocolatey batter forms, then pour into your lined tin. Bake in the centre of the oven for 50 mins- 1 hr until the cake begins to shrink from the sides of the tin and it is springy to touch. Leave to cool in its tin."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once cool, remove the cake from its tin and make the icing. Sieve the icing sugar into a bowl, add all the remaining icing ingredients then using an electric whisk, whisk together until a smooth frosting forms. (It's really important both the cream cheese and butter are at room temp so they mix together nicely!)"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spread the icing all across the top of the cake and cut into fat slices to serve."
    }
  ],
